So let's mobilize and unite. Let's educate those that are curious and be patient when theyâ€™re ready. I'm a firm believer and this is why I'm all in on this space.

We are in a paradigm shift. A transition from a traditional/centralized world to a brave/decentralized one. One that is egoless and permissionless. We have the keys and authority to build it together. But with great opportunity comes great responsibility.

I think NFTs are a great entry point into what is possible in the broader metaverse moving forward.

TL;DR: As much as I loved my previous work, there's simply no way I'm going to miss this opportunity. This is what I've been waiting for my entire life.
We have the technology, the resource, and most importantly the community to build with!

This is our opportunity to build multiple versions of Manhattan, Los Angeles, London, Paris and Tokyo. Multiple versions of Earth and Mars. Then the community can decide governance, structure and allocation

In this generation's version, all are invited to build and participate. It is not limited or restricted by class or invite. And while I (and many others) feel like we have missed out on things in the past, if you are reading this, you are still early to Web3.

Conclusion: My interpretation of Web3 and the broader metaverse is this is the digital version of the "Industrial Revolution." We were not born in the late 17 or 1800s. And our last names are not Rockefeller or Carnegie nor are we freemasons.

A passionate culture collector, community member, and financial technologist. It slapped me in the face and immediately struck me that all those times I feel like I missed the boat on something led me up to this very moment.
